  "prompt": "If I connect USB OTG pendrive to my power bank and connect the other point with data cable to my mobile, will pendrive be working on my mobile?",
  "response": "Connecting a USB OTG (On-The-Go) pen drive to a power bank and then connecting your mobile device to the power bank with a data cable generally won't work for accessing the pen drive on your mobile. Here's why:\n\n1. **OTG Functionality**: USB OTG allows your mobile device to act as a host for USB devices like pen drives. For this to work, the pen drive needs to be directly connected to the mobile device's USB port.\n\n2. **Power Bank Role**: A power bank is primarily designed to provide power to devices, not to facilitate data transfer. When you connect a pen drive to a power bank, the power bank will supply power to the pen drive, but it won't allow your mobile device to communicate with the pen drive.\n\n3. **Direct Connection Needed**: To use the pen drive with your mobile, you should connect the pen drive directly to the mobile device's USB port (using an OTG adapter if necessary). \n\nIn summary, for your USB OTG pen drive to work with your mobile, it must be connected directly to the mobile device, not through a power bank.",
